### loadModuleForTwoRounds() {#aedbd5b8bb99f2c1816738f4687a3b43a}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>std::unique&#95;ptr&lt; Module &gt; llvm::cgdata::loadModuleForTwoRounds (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/bitcodemodule">BitcodeModule</a> &amp; OrigModule, unsigned Task, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/llvmcontext">LLVMContext</a> &amp; Context, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/arrayref">ArrayRef</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> &gt; IRFiles)</>}>
Load the optimized bitcode module for the second codegen round.

<code>OrigModule</code> is the original bitcode module. <code>Task</code> identifies the partition number in the parallel code generation process. <code>Context</code> provides the environment settings for module operations. <code>IRFiles</code> contains optimized bitcode module files needed for loading. 
<SectionUser title="Returns">
A unique&#95;ptr to the loaded <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/module">Module</a>, or nullptr if loading fails.
</SectionUser>
